#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Māra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Godhikasutta "
msgstr "23. With Godhika "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.121, pts2ed1.265, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.23:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.23:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā godhiko isigilipasse viharati kāḷasilāyaṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Godhika was staying on the slopes of Isigili at the Black Rock. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Godhika, meditating diligent, keen, and resolute, experienced temporary freedom of heart. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi. "
msgstr "But then he fell away from that temporary freedom of heart. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "For a second … "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.8"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "third … "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.9"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā … pe … parihāyi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.10"
msgid "Catutthampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto … pe … vimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "fourth … "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.11"
msgid "Catutthampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā … pe … parihāyi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.12"
msgid "Pañcamampi kho āyasmā godhiko … pe … cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "fifth … "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.13"
msgid "Pañcamampi kho āyasmā … pe … vimuttiyā parihāyi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.14"
msgid "Chaṭṭhampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "sixth time Godhika experienced temporary freedom of heart. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.15"
msgid "Chaṭṭhampi kho āyasmā godhiko tamhā sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihāyi. "
msgstr "But for a sixth time he fell away from it. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:1.16"
msgid "Sattamampi kho āyasmā godhiko appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto sāmayikaṃ cetovimuttiṃ phusi. "
msgstr "For a seventh time Godhika, meditating diligent, keen, and resolute, experienced temporary freedom of heart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.266, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.23:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato godhikassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then he thought, "

msgctxt "sn4.23:2.2"
msgid "“yāva chaṭṭhaṃ khvāhaṃ sāmayikāya cetovimuttiyā parihīno. "
msgstr "“I’ve fallen away from this temporary freedom of heart no less than six times. "

msgctxt "sn4.23:2.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ satthaṃ āhareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I slit my wrists?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā āyasmato godhikassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "And then Māra the Wicked, knowing what Godhika was thinking, went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.1"
msgid "“Mahāvīra mahāpañña, "
msgstr "“O great hero, O greatly wise! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.2"
msgid "iddhiyā yasasā jala; "
msgstr "Shining with power and glory. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.3"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātīta, "
msgstr "You’ve gone beyond all threats and perils, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:3.4"
msgid "pāde vandāmi cakkhuma. "
msgstr "I bow to your feet, O seer! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.1"
msgid "Sāvako te mahāvīra, "
msgstr "Great hero, master of death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.2"
msgid "maraṇaṃ maraṇābhibhū; "
msgstr "your disciple longs for death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.3"
msgid "Ākaṅkhati cetayati, "
msgstr "he’s planning for it. "

# NOTE: A rather curious epithet for Mara to use. It is identical with “Lucifer”. http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=lucifer
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:4.4"
msgid "taṃ nisedha jutindhara. "
msgstr "Stop him, O light-bringer! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.1"
msgid "Kathañhi bhagavā tuyhaṃ, "
msgstr "For how, Blessed One, can a disciple of yours, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.2"
msgid "Sāvako sāsane rato; "
msgstr "one who loves your teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.3"
msgid "Appattamānaso sekkho, "
msgstr "a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:5.4"
msgid "Kālaṃ kayirā janesutā”ti. "
msgstr "take his own life, O renowned one?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn4.23:6.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmatā godhikena satthaṃ āharitaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Godhika had already slit his wrists. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:6.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.267, sc7
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.1"
msgid "“Evañhi dhīrā kubbanti, "
msgstr "“This is how the wise act, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.2"
msgid "nāvakaṅkhanti jīvitaṃ; "
msgstr "for they don’t long for life. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, "
msgstr "Having plucked out craving, root and all, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:7.4"
msgid "godhiko parinibbuto”ti. "
msgstr "Godhika is extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn4.23:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn4.23:8.2"
msgid "“āyāma, bhikkhave, yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkamissāma yattha godhikena kulaputtena satthaṃ āharitan”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, mendicants, let’s go to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili where Godhika, who came from a good family, slit his wrists.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:8.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.122, sc9
msgctxt "sn4.23:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha together with several mendicants went to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/turning-shoulders-and-casting-off-aggregates/2949
#. VAR: semānaṃ → soppamānaṃ (si, mr) | seyyamānaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.23:9.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ godhikaṃ dūratova mañcake vivattakkhandhaṃ semānaṃ. "
msgstr "The Buddha saw Godhika off in the distance lying on his cot, having cast off the aggregates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:9.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva purimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ, gacchati adho, gacchati anudisaṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time a cloud of black smoke was moving east, west, north, south, above, below, and in-between. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.268, sc10
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.2"
msgid "“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva purimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ, gacchati adho, gacchati anudisan”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you see that cloud of black smoke moving east, west, north, south, above, below, and in-between?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.4"
msgid "“Eso kho, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā godhikassa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ samanvesati: "
msgstr "“That’s Māra the Wicked searching for Godhika’s consciousness, wondering: "

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.5"
msgid "‘kattha godhikassa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ patiṭṭhitan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Where is Godhika’s consciousness established?’ "

msgctxt "sn4.23:10.6"
msgid "Appatiṭṭhitena ca, bhikkhave, viññāṇena godhiko kulaputto parinibbuto”ti. "
msgstr "But since his consciousness is not established, Godhika is extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.23:10.7"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā beluvapaṇḍuvīṇaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra, carrying his harp of yellow wood apple, went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.1"
msgid "“Uddhaṃ adho ca tiriyaṃ, "
msgstr "“Above, below, and all around, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.2"
msgid "disā anudisā svahaṃ; "
msgstr "in the four quarters and in-between, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.3"
msgid "Anvesaṃ nādhigacchāmi, "
msgstr "I’ve been searching without success: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:11.4"
msgid "godhiko so kuhiṃ gato”ti. "
msgstr "where has that Godhika got to?” "

# NOTE: reading so
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
#. VAR: Yo → so (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.1"
msgid "“Yo dhīro dhitisampanno, "
msgstr "“He was a wise and steadfast sage, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.2"
msgid "jhāyī jhānarato sadā; "
msgstr "a meditator who loved to practice absorption. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.3"
msgid "Ahorattaṃ anuyuñjaṃ, "
msgstr "By day and by night he applied himself, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:12.4"
msgid "jīvitaṃ anikāmayaṃ. "
msgstr "without concern for his life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.1"
msgid "Jetvāna maccuno senaṃ, "
msgstr "He defeated the army of death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.2"
msgid "anāgantvā punabbhavaṃ; "
msgstr "and won’t return for any future life. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha, "
msgstr "Having plucked out craving root and all "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:13.4"
msgid "godhiko parinibbuto”ti. "
msgstr "Godhika is extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.269, sc14
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.1"
msgid "Tassa sokaparetassa, "
msgstr "Stricken with sorrow, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.2"
msgid "vīṇā kacchā abhassatha; "
msgstr "his harp dropping from his armpit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.3"
msgid "Tato so dummano yakkho, "
msgstr "that spirit, downcast, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tatthevantaradhāyathāti → tatthevantaradhāyithāti (s1-3, km) | tatthevantaradhayathāti (pts1) | tattheva antaradhāyīti (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.23:14.4"
msgid "tatthevantaradhāyathāti. "
msgstr "vanished right there."

